article.description: — Hyunjung Lee had 12 points and 10 rebounds to carry Davidson to a 70-46 win over William & Mary on Saturday.
article.headline: Lee's double-double sends Davidson past William & Mary 70-46
article.linkText: Lee's double-double sends Davidson past William & Mary 70-46
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- — Hyunjung Lee had 12 points and 10 rebounds to carry Davidson to a 70-46 win over William & Mary on Saturday. Luka Brajkovic had 16 points and seven rebounds for the Wildcats (6-2), who stretched their winning streak to five games. Foster Loyer added 15 points. Connor Kochera had 18 points and nine rebounds for the Tribe (1-8). Yuri Covington added 14 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Portions of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
